---
const stats = [
  { n: '42', l: 'MCP tools + 3 resources' },
  { n: '3×3', l: 'OS × Python, all passing' },
  { n: '0', l: 'runtime dependencies' },
  { n: 'Apache 2.0', l: 'licensed, explicit patent grant' },
];
---

<section class="section receipts">
  <div class="media-bg" aria-hidden="true">
    <img src="/media/hero/soul_v2.png" alt="" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    <div class="scrim"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <p class="kicker reveal reveal-sm">Maturity</p>
    <h2 class="reveal">Stable, with receipts.</h2>
    <p class="sub reveal">
      Every quality gate is publicly verifiable: the test suite passes on Ubuntu, macOS, and Windows
      across Python 3.11–3.13; the Windows wrapper is <em>executed</em>, not simulated; cold starts
      are proven on both host shapes; and the quickstart runs against the published package in a
      clean CI environment on every push.
    </p>

    <div class="stats">
      {
        stats.map((s) => (
          <div class="stat reveal">
            <span class="n">{s.n}</span>
            <span class="l">{s.l}</span>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>

    <p class="note reveal">
      Markdown is the source of truth. The graph index is a disposable cache rebuilt on demand. If
      they ever disagree, Markdown wins.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .receipts {
    background: var(--ink-800);
  }
  .media-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    z-index: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .media-bg img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
  .scrim {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background:
      radial-gradient(120% 80% at 30% 50%, transparent 30%, rgba(7, 8, 12, 0.92) 100%),
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(7, 8, 12, 0.5), rgba(7, 8, 12, 0.85));
  }
  .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .sub {
    max-width: 50rem;
    color: var(--cream-200);
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 1.7vw, 1.18rem);
    margin: 0 0 2.6rem;
  }
  .stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 12rem), 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .stat {
    border: 1px solid var(--edge);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    background: rgba(11, 13, 18, 0.6);
    backdrop-filter: blur(6px);
    padding: 1.6rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    transition:
      transform 0.18s ease,
      border-color 0.18s ease;
  }
  .stat:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.35);
  }
  .stat .n {
    font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    /* Solid, high-contrast figures instead of glowing accent numerals —
       the receipts read as facts, not a marketing metric wall. */
    color: var(--cream-50);
  }
  .stat .l {
    color: var(--cream-200);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .note {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    max-width: 46rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--amber-500);
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }
</style>
